    Let <fr:tex>u\colon  X\to  Y</fr:tex> be a continuous map between topological spaces.
    We say that <fr:tex>u</fr:tex> is <fr:em>proper</fr:em> if it is proper in the sense of Bourbaki (i.e. universally closed) and furthermore separated (i.e. the diagonal of <fr:tex>X\times _Y X</fr:tex> is closed).
  </fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
