root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1893</fr:anchor><fr:addr>hodge-theory-iii-0.4</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-0.4.xml</fr:route><fr:number>III.0.4</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-terminology-and-notation</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
    A <fr:em>mixed Hodge <fr:tex>A</fr:tex>-structure</fr:em> consists of an <fr:tex>A</fr:tex>-module <fr:tex>H_A</fr:tex> of finite type, a finite increasing filtration <fr:tex>W</fr:tex> on the <fr:tex>A\otimes \mathbb {Q}</fr:tex>-vector space <fr:tex>H_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}=H_A\otimes \mathbb {Q}</fr:tex>, and a finite decreasing filtration <fr:tex>F</fr:tex> on the <fr:tex>\mathbb {C}</fr:tex>-vector space <fr:tex>H_\mathbb {C}=H_A\otimes _A\mathbb {C}</fr:tex>.
    We demand that the <fr:tex>(\operatorname {Gr}_n^W(H_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}),\operatorname {Gr}_n^W(F))</fr:tex> be Hodge <fr:tex>A\otimes \mathbb {Q}</fr:tex>-structures.
    For <fr:tex>A=\mathbb {Z}</fr:tex> (resp. <fr:tex>A=\mathbb {Q}</fr:tex>), we recover <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.1"
href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.1.xml"
taxon="Definition"
number="2.3.1"></fr:ref> (resp. <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.8"
href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.8.xml"
number="2.3.8"></fr:ref>);
    the results of <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3"
href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.xml"
number="2.3"></fr:ref> carry over as they are.
  </fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
